## Key architectural decisions (chronological)
1. **CRF** (02-14): +0.016 kappa over no-CRF. Linear CRF only (semi-Markov tested, no benefit).
2. **Frozen encoder** (02-20): CKA=0.966 between pretrained/finetuned -- finetuning barely changes encoder. Frozen with --freeze-epochs 999 is default.
3. **CE removal** (02-20): -0.008 kappa but removes label dependency from encoder. Adopted.
4. **SupCon removal** (02-21): -0.014 cumulative from v4. Encoder now fully unsupervised (recon only).
5. **DANN removal** (02-21): z-normalized recon already domain-invariant. DANN fought useful signal.
6. **Proj removal** (02-21): 448->256 L2-normed projection was contrastive vestige. Direct features better for recon.
7. **SE removal** (02-22): Downstream kappa identical to 4 decimal places with/without. 101K wasted params.
8. **STFT 128d** (02-22): 64->128d, encoder 668K->777K. Better recon, downstream wash. Kept for representation quality.

## Data sanitization (02-16)
Dropped 7,735 bad epochs (0.29%): 5,413 flat-line (std<1e-6), 2,322 extreme artifact (>5% samples >20 sigma).
2 subjects fully removed (100% flat). N1 F1 +0.021, N3 F1 +0.018 after cleanup.

