2026-02-23: Residual analysis + encoder metric refactor
================================================================

## Residual analysis findings
Ran reconstruction residual analysis (51K test epochs) + per-stage kNN embedding analysis (20K subsample).

### Reconstruction bottleneck by stage (relative error = MSE/signal_power)
| Stage | Spec RelErr | Wave RelErr | kNN F1 | Downstream F1 |
|-------|-------------|-------------|--------|---------------|
| N1    | 0.718       | 0.570       | 0.473  | 0.516         |
| REM   | 0.663       | 0.588       | 0.513  | 0.829         |
| N2    | 0.495       | 0.373       | 0.779  | 0.813         |
| W     | 0.385       | 0.157       | 0.890  | 0.933         |
| N3    | 0.228       | 0.146       | 0.713  | 0.741         |

Key: N1 has highest relative recon error AND worst kNN/downstream F1.
BiGRU+CRF rescues REM (0.51->0.83 via temporal context) but barely helps N1 (0.47->0.52).
Downstream kappa (0.758) only +0.008 above kNN acc (0.750) -- encoder is the ceiling.

### Spectral band error (spec decoder MSE)
delta (1.00) >> theta (0.95) >> alpha (0.82) >> sigma (0.72) >> beta (0.42) >> gamma (0.19)
Waveform residual power: delta 41% + theta 30% = 71% of residual.

### Embedding geometry
- N1-REM centroid distance: 1.40 (closest pair, vs W-N3=6.13 most distant)
- Intra-class spread ~12 vs inter-centroid 1.4-6.1 -- massive overlap
- PCA: theta/alpha/sigma/beta all load onto same PC (PC1). Encoder merges these
  into one "high-freq axis" instead of independently representing each band.
  For N1/REM separation, theta and alpha need independent axes:
  N1=theta UP + alpha DOWN, REM=theta UP + alpha variable, W=theta LOW + alpha UP.

### Diagnosis
1. N1 is the critical bottleneck: lowest signal power, highest relative error, worst F1.
2. theta/alpha not independently encoded -- merged into single PC. Band decoders
   would create separate gradients forcing independent representation.
3. Spec decoder (1.15M params, larger than encoder) dominates gradient bandwidth
   at weight=0.5. Reducing to 0.3 frees capacity for band-specific targets.

## val_knn metric refactor
Changed val_knn from kNN accuracy to kNN Cohen's kappa across train_encoder.py,
eval_embeddings.py, compare_encoders.py. Rationale: kappa penalizes class-imbalance
shortcuts and weights confusion patterns, directly comparable to downstream kappa.
Also added val_knn_f1 (macro F1) as secondary metric. Silhouette(dataset) retained
for domain invariance monitoring.

2026-02-23: Runtime profiling + speedups
================================================================

## Runtime profiling + speedups
Profiled both training loops with PyTorch profiler (10-20 batches each).

Encoder bottlenecks (batch_size=2048, epoch_mode):
- Convolution fwd+bwd: 56% CUDA time (expected, core compute)
- NCHW->NHWC format conversion: 8.1% (cuDNN Conv1d promotes to 2d; can't fix with channels_last)
- Data loading: 2% (not a bottleneck)

Downstream bottlenecks (batch_size=32, seq_len=200):
- Kernel launch overhead: 272K launches/20 batches, 18% CPU time in cudaLaunchKernel
- GPU utilization: only 1.26 GB peak at bs=32 (massively underutilized)
- NCHW->NHWC: 5% CUDA time

Applied speedups:
| Change | Target | Speedup |
|--------|--------|---------|
| AMP fp16 (precision="16-mixed") | Encoder | 1.32x (0.224s->0.170s/batch) |
| AMP fp16 | Downstream | (marginal compute, mainly batch size) |
| cudnn.benchmark=True | Both | 1.07x encoder (auto-tunes conv algos) |
| batch_size 32->48 | Downstream | 1.88x throughput (18K->35K ep/s) |

Combined: encoder ~1.32x, downstream ~1.88x.
VRAM: encoder 14.3->9.8 GB (AMP saves memory), downstream 1.3->11.2 GB (bigger batches)

2026-02-23: AMP + CRF instability finding
================================================================
AMP fp16 causes downstream divergence (loss explosion to 7-9, best kappa ~0.694 at
epoch 1 then collapse). Root cause: CRF log-sum-exp overflows in fp16 range.
Both baseline and medium branch diverged identically with AMP+CRF. Fix: reverted
downstream train_model.py to fp32 (encoder keeps AMP, no CRF there).

