2026-02-24: v12 -- val_knn bias fix (shuffle=True)
================================================================

## Changes
1. **val_dataloader shuffle=True**: fixed biased val_knn measurement. Previously val loader was
   unshuffled, so kNN only ever saw the first ~6144 epochs (same subjects every epoch).
   Now samples random subset each epoch -- unbiased kNN estimate.
2. **on_load_checkpoint**: added reverse of on_save_checkpoint for torch.compile resume.
   Checkpoint saves strip _orig_mod prefix; on_load re-adds it when encoder is compiled.
   Without this, resuming compiled training crashes with key mismatch.

