| N2 F1 | 0.811 | 0.812 | +0.001 |
| REM F1 | 0.818 | 0.820 | +0.002 |

Verdict: wash/slightly negative. N1 actually worse (-0.018). Fused band decoders don't help
because existing per-branch decoders (128d -> band) already provide sufficient band-specific
gradients. Reconstructing from fused representation forces redundant computation.

## Conclusion
Both dead ends confirmed at full scale. Original ablation-era entries were directionally correct.
Cleaned up: deleted gap_test/fused_band checkpoints+logs, removed experimental code.

