## Ideas evaluated (not implemented -- critical analysis):
- Factorized latent space (z_stage/z_subject/z_device): unidentifiable without labels
- Counterfactual device transfer: no paired cross-device data, domain shift already solved
- Physiology token pretraining: no device-agnostic event detector exists
- Dynamic CRF (circadian/elapsed-time conditioning): position emb test falsified
- Two-head (stage + transition): derived labels add no new signal; Semi-Markov already failed
- Uncertainty-aware soft labels: softening N1 teaches "be uncertain about N1" (wrong direction)
- Temperature scaling: changes CRF emission/transition balance, not a clean calibration tool
- Test-time adaptation: GroupNorm has no running stats; domain shift already ~0
- Sleep world model (generative Deep HMM): current CRF IS state estimation; disc. wins at scale

## Queued explorations
- VICReg branch covariance penalty (encoder retrain required):
  Targets diagnosed failure: theta/alpha collapse onto same PC (residual analysis 2026-02-23).
  Force each of 640 embedding dims to carry independent info via off-diagonal cov penalty.
  Expected: +0.005-0.015 kappa if theta/alpha disentanglement improves N1/REM separation.
- Trajectory dynamics auxiliary loss (downstream, no encoder retrain):
  Next-embed prediction head: Linear(384,640) on BiGRU output predicts encoder embed at t+1.
  Weighted by backward embedding change to upweight onset, downweight exit.
  Expected: modest N1 onset improvement (+0.005 N1 F1), uncertain exit interaction.

