Analysis:
  gru384: Only winner (+0.003 kappa, +0.004 F1, +0.012 N1 F1). Capacity scaling continues.
    192->256 (+0.008), 256->384 (+0.003). Diminishing returns but still positive.
    4.56M trainable params (2x baseline) -- not overfitting yet.
  crf_prior: Wash (+0.001 kappa). AASM priors helped early convergence (lower loss ep0)
    but CRF learns correct transitions regardless within a few epochs.
  seg5/seg6: Both regressed (-0.002 kappa). More segments = less spectral resolution
    per segment. N1 detection worsened in both, confirming 3 segments (10s each) is
    the right granularity for capturing alpha dropout dynamics.
  cross_epoch_conv: Regression (-0.003 kappa, -0.005 N1 F1). Residual Conv1d(64,64,k=5)
    over N1Aux features before GRU adds noise rather than useful local contrast.
    BiGRU already captures temporal context bidirectionally.

Dead ends added: n_segments>3, CRF transition priors, cross-epoch conv

