## 2026-03-01: Information flow trace + test-time inference analysis

### Info flow trace (trace_info_flow.py)
Layer-by-layer kNN probing of stage discriminability at each transform point.
Per-epoch probes (no temporal context, kNN k=5, 5-fold CV, 15K subsample):
  Spectral raw (18d)        kappa=0.503  N1 F1=0.218
  Spectral MLP (128d)       kappa=0.570  N1 F1=0.252  (+0.067)
  STFT branch (128d)        kappa=0.566  N1 F1=0.232
  Encoder spec+STFT (256d)  kappa=0.591  N1 F1=0.260  (+0.025)
  N1Aux raw (24d)           kappa=0.343  N1 F1=0.121
  N1Aux output (64d)        kappa=0.546  N1 F1=0.280
  Pre-GRU combined (320d)   kappa=0.608  N1 F1=0.303  (+0.017 from N1Aux)
Sequence probes (with temporal context):
  BiGRU output (768d) kNN   kappa=0.793  N1 F1=0.510  (+0.185 from GRU context)
  Argmax logits              kappa=0.758  N1 F1=0.553  (-0.035 head compression)
  CRF Viterbi                kappa=0.772  N1 F1=0.537  (+0.014 CRF, -0.015 N1)

Key findings:
- BiGRU is the dominant component: +0.185 kappa, +0.207 N1 F1
- Per-epoch features plateau at kappa=0.608 (ceiling without temporal context)
- Per-stage heads lose 0.035 kappa vs kNN on raw GRU features (768d->5d compression)
- CRF helps overall (+0.014 kappa) but hurts N1 (-0.015 F1)
- N1Aux earns its keep: +0.017 kappa, +0.043 N1 F1 per-epoch

### Test-time overlapping inference (test_overlap.py)
Overlapping windows + full-night single pass on 335 held-out test subjects (393642 epochs).
  stride=200 (1x)  CRF vote  kappa=0.768  N1=0.538
  stride=50 (4x)   CRF vote  kappa=0.771  N1=0.540
  stride=20 (10x)  CRF vote  kappa=0.771  N1=0.538
  Full night CRF             kappa=0.771  N1=0.536
  stride=50 (4x)   logit avg kappa=0.760  N1=0.557
  stride=20 (10x)  logit avg kappa=0.760  N1=0.558

Key findings:
- Overlapping inference is a dead end for kappa (+0.003 max, within noise)
- Full-night GRU adds nothing over 200-epoch windows
- CRF suppresses N1 by ~0.020 F1 across all configs (confirmed independently)
- N1 ceiling without CRF: 0.558 (logit avg) vs 0.537 (CRF)
- Coverage: 393642/393642 vs baseline DataLoader's 359400 (8.7% more epochs, no help)

### Assessment
Model is at diminishing returns for this architecture. Next meaningful jump requires
either cleaner labels, fundamentally different approach, or accepting CRF/N1 tradeoff.
CRF costs 0.020 N1 F1 to gain 0.011 kappa -- tradeoff depends on application.

## 2026-03-01: N1Aux Ablation (full training, gru_hidden=384)

### Setup
- Removed N1AuxFeatures (64d) from downstream pipeline (GRU input: 256d instead of 320d)
- Same config: gru_hidden=384, freeze_epochs=999, batch_size=48, max_epochs=40, seed=42
- Trainable params: 4.39M (vs 4.56M with N1Aux, -170K)

### Results
| Metric   | no_n1aux | baseline | Delta  |
|----------|----------|----------|--------|
| test_kappa | 0.768  | 0.772    | -0.004 |
| test_f1    | 0.774  | 0.779    | -0.005 |
| N1 F1      | 0.516  | 0.537    | -0.021 |
| REM F1     | 0.841  | 0.849    | -0.008 |
| W F1       | 0.937  | 0.933    | +0.004 |
| N2 F1      | 0.822  | 0.824    | -0.002 |
| N3 F1      | 0.752  | 0.752    | 0.000  |
| val peak   | 0.774 (ep9) | 0.776 (ep12) | -0.002 |

### Conclusion
N1Aux earns its 24K params. The -0.021 N1 F1 hit is exactly what it was designed to prevent.
Also hurts REM (-0.008), likely from shared spectral entropy/dynamics features.
N1AuxFeatures is not dead weight -- keep it.

## 2026-03-01: Model Simplification

### Motivation
Hard audit of every component. N1Aux contributes +0.004 kappa / +0.021 N1 F1 but at
170K effective params (24K module + 147K GRU widening). User accepts the loss for simpler model.
Also found: CNN branches computed every forward pass then discarded (pure waste),
per-stage heads (5x redundant LayerNorm+Dropout on same input, 246K params).

### Changes
1. **Removed N1AuxFeatures** - deleted class (~100 lines), GRU input 320d -> 256d
2. **Skip CNN in forward** - _encode() calls encoder.spectral() + encoder.stft() directly,
   skips 3 CNN branches (~870K frozen params, ~77 GFLOPS/batch saved)
3. **Shared head** - replaced 5 per-stage MLPs (246K) with single MLP (49K):
   Dropout -> LayerNorm(768) -> Linear(768,64) -> GELU -> Linear(64,5)
4. **torch.compile** now targets individual branches instead of whole encoder
5. Updated test_overlap.py, trace_info_flow.py to match

### Param count
- Before: 4.56M trainable (5.64M total)
- After: 4.19M trainable (5.26M total), -8.2% trainable

### Results (exp-name: simplified)
| Metric   | simplified | baseline | Delta  |
|----------|------------|----------|--------|
| test_kappa | 0.765    | 0.772    | -0.007 |
| test_f1    | 0.777    | 0.779    | -0.002 |
| N1 F1      | 0.535    | 0.537    | -0.002 |
| N2 F1      | 0.820    | 0.829    | -0.009 |
| W F1       | 0.932    | 0.938    | -0.006 |
| N3 F1      | 0.753    | 0.748    | +0.005 |
| REM F1     | 0.844    | 0.843    | +0.001 |
| Speed      | 4.42 it/s | ~3.0 it/s | +47%  |
| val peak   | 0.773 (ep9) | 0.776 (ep12) | -0.003 |

### Analysis
- Kappa -0.007 = N1Aux removal (-0.004) + shared head (-0.003)
- F1 barely affected (-0.002): shared head recovers N1 F1 that per-stage heads lose
- N1 F1: simplified 0.535 vs no_n1aux (per-stage) 0.516 -- shared head +0.019 for N1
- 47% training speedup from skipping CNN forward pass
- Checkpoint: checkpoints/sleep_model/simplified/epoch=9-val_kappa=0.773.ckpt
2026-03-01: N1-targeted experiments
================================================================

### Experiment 1: Directional STFT pool + delta features (FAILED)
- DirectionalSTFTPool: first/last half delta of STFT transformer tokens
- Delta features: epoch-to-epoch spectral change with Linear(512,256) projection
- Result: kappa=0.756 (-0.009), N1 F1=0.492 (-0.043) -- WORSE
- Root cause: lossy projections destroyed information; epoch-to-epoch deltas
  noise-dominated; frozen transformer tokens lack temporal ordering after self-attention

### Experiment 2: Attention pooling + wider head (SUCCESS)
- AttentionPool: learned weighted average over 31 STFT frames (129 params, temp-scaled)
- Wider head bottleneck: 768->128->5 (was 768->64->5)
- Result: kappa=0.768 (+0.003), F1=0.779 (+0.002), N1 F1=0.540 (+0.005)
- All stages improved or held; training collapsed at epoch 12 (attention saturation)
  but best checkpoint at epoch 9 was clean
- Temperature scaling (dim^-0.5) added to prevent future collapse

### Experiment 3: No-CRF ablation (INFORMATIVE)
- Same architecture as Exp 2, CRF disabled
- Result: kappa=0.756 (-0.009), N1 F1=0.546 (+0.011), N2 F1=0.806 (-0.014)
- N1 recall 62.6% (vs 55.3% baseline) -- CRF suppresses brief N1 episodes
- CRF's N1 penalty now -0.006 (was -0.020 historically); attention pooling reduces CRF/N1 conflict
- 2.3x faster without CRF (10.13 vs 4.36 it/s)

### Summary table
| Config               | kappa | F1    | N1 F1 | N2 F1 | N3 F1 |
|----------------------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|
| simplified baseline  | 0.765 | 0.777 | 0.535 | 0.820 | 0.753 |
| directional+delta    | 0.756 | 0.762 | 0.492 | 0.814 | 0.731 |
| attn_pool+CRF        | 0.768 | 0.779 | 0.540 | 0.821 | 0.755 |
| attn_pool-CRF        | 0.756 | 0.773 | 0.546 | 0.806 | 0.747 |

### Current best: attn_pool+CRF
- Checkpoint: checkpoints/sleep_model/attn_pool/epoch=9-val_kappa=0.771.ckpt
- Per-class: W=0.937, N1=0.540, N2=0.821, N3=0.755, REM=0.843
- 4.2M trainable, +49K from wider head + 129 from attention pool

